'''Nesheim''' is a village in [[Vaksdal]] municipality in [[Hordaland]] county, [[Norway]].  The village is located in the upper part of the [[Eksingedalen]] valley, along the river Storelvi.  The village sits at the intersection of two roads: County Road 344 which runs through the whole valley and County Road 313 which crosses the mountains into the next valley to the south, Teigdalen (in [[Voss]]).  Nesheim is the site of [[Nesheim Church]].

